\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. D. viscosa} (L.) W. Greuter,{\i  Exsicc. Genav.}{\b  4}: 71 (1973) ({\i Inula viscosa} (L.) Aiton). Densely glandular, viscid perennial 40-130 cm; stems woody at base. Lower leaves 30-70 × 2-30 mm, linear to oblong-lanceolate, acute, remotely denticulate; upper sessile, semiamplexicaul. Capitula medium; involucre 6-8 mm; outer bracts 1-2 × 0·5-0·7 mm, linear-lanceolate, acute, erect; inner 6-8 × 0·6-0·8 mm. Ligules 10-12 mm, distinctly exceeding the involucre. Achenes c. 2 mm, hairy; pappus with 15 setae. 2n = 18, 34.{\i  Waste places. S. Europe.} Al Bl Bu Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si Tu.
\par 
\par 
\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b viscosa}: Stems erect; leaves 30-60 × 4-30 mm, oblong-lanceolate; margin flat.{\i  Throughout the range of the species, except S.W. Portugal.}
