\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b revoluta} (Hoffmanns. & Link) P. Silva & Tutin,{\i  Bot. Jour. Linn. Soc.}{\b  67}: 282 (1973) ({\i Inula revoluta} Hoffmanns. & Link): Stems often procumbent; leaves 60-70 × 2-3 mm, linear; margin revolute.{\i  S.W. Portugal}.
