\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. P. paludosa} Link in Schrader,{\i  Neues Jour. Bot.}{\b  1}({\b 3}): 142 (1806). Like {\b 3} but middle and upper leaves linear to narrowly oblong, rigid, not or scarcely undulate; inner involucral bracts acute; ligules up to 3 mm longer than the involucre, sometimes patent; achene c. 1 mm, with erecto-patent hairs. 2n = 18+0-1 B.{\i  Seasonally wet places. • Iberian peninsula.} Hs.Lu.
