\pard\f0\fs28  {\b  P. microcephala} Lange, {\i Bol. Soc. Brot. }{\b 1}: 42, 50 (1883), described from W. Portugal (Ilha Berlenga), is a dwarf much branched plant with leaves mostly less than 5 mm long and very numerous capitula 0·4-0·5 cm in diameter; it is probably a variant of {\b 4}, but further investigation is needed. A similar variant has been collected once in S.W. Spain (S.W. of Cádiz).
