\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. P. sicula} (L.) Moris,{\i  Fl. Sard.}{\b  2}: 363 (1840-1843). Like {\b 3} but middle and upper leaves linear, rigid, not undulate; peduncles up to 4 cm, thickened after anthesis; involucral bracts rather sparsely pubescent and glandular, the inner subacute; pappus-hairs 18-25, the scales connate at the base only; achene rather densely appressed-hairy.{\i  Seasonally damp places. Mediterranean region.} Al Bl Co Cr Ga Hs It Sa Si Tu.
